# 16-Week Cybersecurity Workbook
Time budget: 4–6 hours/week
Goal: Build practical defensive network/system security skills and create a portable assessment workflow.

## Rules
- Only test systems/networks you own or are explicitly authorized to assess.
- Keep lab testing isolated from normal home use.
- Document everything.
- Focus on understanding first, tools second.

## Core Outcomes
By the end, I should be able to:
- map a network
- identify devices and services
- understand exposure
- capture and inspect traffic
- perform safe authorized scanning
- write a basic security report
- design safer remote access using Tailscale/WireGuard concepts
- use a portable USB toolkit for defensive assessment

---

# Week 1 — Build your notebook and network map

## Goals
- Create a place for notes
- Draw the home network
- Build an asset inventory

## Theory
Learn:
- LAN
- WAN
- NAT
- DHCP
- DNS
- gateway
- private IP addresses
- ports

## Tasks
- Create a local notes folder
- Create folders:
  - notes/
  - diagrams/
  - scans/
  - captures/
  - reports/
  - scripts/
- Draw a simple network diagram
- Create an asset inventory table with:
  - device name
  - device type
  - OS
  - wired/wifi
  - role/purpose
- Write 5–10 lines: “How my home network works”

## Deliverable
- network diagram
- asset inventory
- short summary note

## Checkpoint
Can I explain my network in plain English?

