# Week 2 — Linux host visibility

## Goals
- Understand what a Linux system is running
- Learn to inspect services and ports

## Theory
Learn:
- process
- service
- daemon
- socket
- listening port
- boot log

## Commands
Run on each Linux machine:
- hostnamectl
- ip a
- ip route
- ss -tulpn
- ps aux
- systemctl list-units --type=service
- journalctl -b --no-pager | head -100

## Tasks
- Save command output into notes
- List all listening services
- Mark each service as:
  - local only
  - LAN reachable
  - unknown
- List 3 things you don’t understand and research them

## Deliverable
- baseline note for each Linux machine

## Checkpoint
Do I know what services are running and why?

---

# Week 3 — Docker and exposure

## Goals
- Understand container exposure
- Check if services are unintentionally reachable

## Theory
Learn:
- container vs VM
- localhost vs 0.0.0.0
- published ports
- bridge networking

## Commands
- docker ps
- docker inspect <container>
- ss -tulpn

## Tasks
- Identify all containers
- Record exposed ports
- Record bind addresses
- Determine whether Postgres is:
