# Week 6 — Nmap fundamentals

## Goals
- Learn host discovery and service enumeration safely

## Theory
Learn:
- host discovery
- open vs closed vs filtered port
- service detection
- why scans can be noisy

## Commands
Use only on systems you own or lab systems:
- nmap -sn <target>
- nmap -sV <target>
- nmap -O <target>

## Tasks
- Scan one Linux VM
- Scan one physical Linux host
- Compare results with ss -tulpn
- Record differences and surprises

## Deliverable
- first discovery report

## Checkpoint
Can I interpret scan results without guessing wildly?

